decks.notes: This deck focuses on fast and aggressive creature plays alongside disruption spells to control the board and pressure the opponent quickly. With Kellan, the Fae-Blooded as the commander, the deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with efficient creatures like Amped Raptor and Swift Reconfiguration, supported by cards like Aether Vial and Stoneforge Mystic to cheat out powerful artifacts like Umezawa's Jitte. The deck also includes removal spells like Lightning Bolt and Swords to Plowshares to deal with threats efficiently. By applying early pressure and disrupting the opponent's game plan, this deck aims to win the game before the opponent can stabilize or set up their own win conditions.

The deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures and burn spells to apply pressure on the opponent, while also disrupting their hand and graveyard with cards like Inquisition of Kozilek, Hymn to Tourach, and Thoughtseize. Flamewar, Brash Veteran serves as the commander, providing a strong aggressive presence on the battlefield. The deck includes a mix of removal spells like Terminate and Dismember, as well as powerful threats like Kroxa, Titan of Death's Hunger and Seasoned Pyromancer. Additionally, the deck includes a variety of mana-fixing lands to ensure smooth mana curve. Overall, the deck aims to quickly overwhelm the opponent with its aggressive creatures and efficient removal spells.

The main concept of this deck is to control the game by ramping up quickly with Azusa, Lost but Seeking and other land-based ramp cards, while disrupting the opponent's strategies with various utility lands and board wipes like All Is Dust. The deck aims to generate value from lands entering the battlefield, utilizing cards like Exploration and Crucible of Worlds to continuously play lands and trigger landfall abilities. By tutoring for key pieces such as Dark Depths and Thespian's Stage, the deck can create powerful combos to win the game. Overall, the strategy revolves around efficient land ramp, resource denial through land destruction, and capitalizing on synergies with land-based threats and utility lands to outvalue and outmaneuver opponents.

This deck focuses on utilizing the power of Partner commanders Thrasios and Tymna to create a versatile aggro strategy. The key concept of this deck is to establish a strong mana base with a mix of mana dorks and fetch lands, allowing for early ramp and fixing. The deck aims to apply early pressure with efficient creatures and disruption, while also having access to powerful tutors and card draw to maintain resources. By combining the aggressive elements of an aggro deck with the flexibility of a partner commander strategy, this deck seeks to overwhelm opponents with a combination of speed, consistency, and resilience on the battlefield.
